Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest chapter

Edit chapters inside an existing `.sdpub` archive.

Usage:
  spinedigest chapter list <path> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter status <path> --chapter <id> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter add <path> --stage <planned|source> [--title <title>] [--parent <id>] [--input <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter move <path> --chapter <id> (--parent <id>|--root|--before <id>|--after <id>|--first|--last) [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter remove <path> --chapter <id> [--recursive] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter reset <path> --chapter <id> --to <planned|source|graph> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter set-source <path> --chapter <id> [--input <path>] --input-format <format> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter set-summary <path> --chapter <id> [--input <path>] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter set-title <path> --chapter <id> (--title <title>|--clear) [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter tree <path> [--json] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter tree apply <path> [--input <path>] [--dry-run] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Chapter stages:
  planned     TOC chapter exists, but no source is stored.
  source      Normalized source text is stored.
  graph       Source plus generated graph are stored.
  summary     Source, graph, and final summary are stored.

Input rules:
  - `<path>` is the `.sdpub` archive edited in place.
  - `--chapter` is the numeric chapter id printed by `list` or `add`.
  - `add --stage planned` creates an empty planned chapter. Use this for chapter directories, groups, and drafting placeholders.
  - `add --stage source` creates a chapter and fills it from `--input <path>` or stdin.
  - `set-source` and `set-summary` read `--input <path>` when provided, otherwise stdin.
  - `set-source` accepts only `txt` or `markdown` for `--input-format`.
  - `set-title --title` renames a chapter in the tree; `set-title --clear` removes the explicit title.
  - `move` changes parent/order only; it does not edit source, graph, or summary data.
  - `tree` prints the chapter tree as JSON with `title: null` for untitled chapters.
  - `tree apply` applies a complete chapter tree JSON. It can reorder chapters and change titles when a node includes `title`.
  - `reset --to` accepts `planned`, `source`, or `graph`.
  - Structure edits, `set-title`, `set-source`, `set-summary`, and `reset` do not call an LLM provider.
  - To generate graph or summary for a chapter, use `spinedigest build <path> --chapter <id> --stage graph --confirm` or `--stage summary --confirm`.
  - Append `--help` after an action for action-specific details, for example `spinedigest chapter reset --help`.

